  "text": "Nowadays many managers or decision maker always face the challenging situation of selecting the right solution for a given decision making problem. In order to handle multiple, convicting values, a class of methodologies has developed over the last 60 years called problem structuring methods (PSM), or soft operational research (OR) methods. These methods are characterized as a family of approaches for supporting decisions by groups of a diverse composition within a complex environment to agree a problem focus and make commitments to a series of actions. They are usually applied to unstructured problems or ill-structured problems characterized by multiple actors, multiple perspectives, conflicting interests, and high levels of uncertainty and can often involve models as transitional objects to aid the decision-making process [CITATION_1] .",
